Frank Lampard has named Timo Werner, Kai Havertz and Hakim Ziyech in his starting XI to face Morecambe in the FA Cup third round. Under pressure following a poor spell of results, the Blues boss has opted to give several senior stars game time in order to regain confidence and form. Kepa Arrizabalaga starts in goal for the Blues. The Spaniard has featured just twice since the arrival of Edouard Mendy from Rennes in the summer transfer window. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The back four is one of experience. Cesar Azpilicueta will captain the side from right back with, somewhat surprisingly, Kurt Zouma next to him. Antonio Rudiger is the Frenchman’s centre-back partner will Emerson at left-back. Billy Gilmour will anchor the midfield and ahead of him will be Mason Mount and Kai Havertz. It is the German’s first start for five matches. PSG Post Threatens To Take Pochettino Down Wrong Path Sokratis Told To Make Decision On His Future After Arteta’s ‘Complicated’ Claim The front three is the most intriguing. Callum Hudson-Odoi’s recent good form is rewarded with a start, and in his favoured role on the left wing. On the right is Hakim Ziyech. The Moroccon international returned from injury against Manchester City last weekend but looked off the pace. This is a chance for him to gain much-needed fitness.